# Cypress Practical Test Framework (UI + API | BDD + POM)

This project demonstrates a Cypress automation framework setup for both **UI and API** test automation using:
- ✅ Cypress + JavaScript
- ✅ Cucumber (BDD)
- ✅ Page Object Model (POM)
- ✅ API Request Testing (Petstore Swagger)
- ✅ Screenshot/Video capture on failure
- ✅ CLI execution with reporting

---

## 📁 Project Structure

## 📁 Project Structure
Cypress_PracticalTest/
├── cypress/
│   ├── e2e/
│   │   ├── ui/
│   │   │   └── features/
│   │   │       ├── login.feature
│   │   │       └── navigation.feature
│   │   ├── api/
│   │   │   └── features/
│   │   │       └── pet.feature
│   ├── support/
│   │   ├── step_definitions/
│   │   │   ├── loginSteps.js
│   │   │   ├── navigationSteps.js
│   │   │   └── petSteps.js
│   │   ├── pageObjects/
│   │   │   ├── LoginPage.js
│   │   │   └── NavigationPage.js
│   │   ├── commands.js
│   │   └── petapi.js
│   ├── fixtures/
│   │   └── example.json
│   ├── screenshots/          ← Captured on test failures
│   ├── videos/               ← Video recordings
│   ├── assets/               ← (Optional) Custom data, mocks, etc.
│
├── mochawesome-report/       ← Final HTML report
├── reports/                  ← Raw JSON files from mochawesome
│   ├── mochawesome.json
│   └── mochawesome.html
│
├── cypress.config.js
├── package.json
├── package-lock.json
├── README.md

| Folder                             | Purpose                                       |
| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `e2e/ui/features/`                 | All UI BDD `.feature` files                   |
| `e2e/api/features/`                | All API `.feature` files                      |
| `step_definitions/`                | Step implementations for UI/API               |
| `pageObjects/`                     | POM files for reusable UI selectors & actions |
| `petapi.js`                        | API helper methods for Pet endpoints          |
| `screenshots/` + `videos/`         | Auto-captured on failures                     |
| `reports/` + `mochawesome-report/` | Raw & final reports                           |
| `cypress.config.js`                | Central config for Cypress and reporter       |




Install Dependencies

npm install

Run Tests:
npx cypress run --spec "cypress/e2e/ui/features/*.feature"
npx cypress run --spec "cypress/e2e/api/features/pet.feature"


Merge JSON reports
npx mochawesome-merge cypress/reports/*.json > mochawesome.json

Generate HTML report
npx marge mochawesome.json -f report -o mochawesome-report

